title: Los Freddy's Obsesion LP (vinyl rip)
description:
This is very old vinyl rip of Los Freddy&#039;s 
"Obsesion" LP from 1968 (?). This LP is 
long OUT-OF-PRINT and was one of my 1st 
attempts at ripping vinyl in 1997.

Quality isn&#039;t great, my family must have 
played this LP nearly 10,000 times before
1980 (!), but it&#039;s now available to any one 
who is interested, or fondly remembers early 
60&#039;s to early 70&#039;s Mexican garage rock &#039;n roll.

"Obsesion" contains a few spanish sung 
cover tunes. 

"Te Esperare" is Dino, Desi & Billy&#039;s
"Tell Someone You Love Them". 

"Abril Llego" and "Vamos YA" are covers 
of The Archies&#039; "Seventeen Ain&#039;t Young" 
and "Boys and Girls". 

"Cuando Tu No Estas" is "Girl Watcher" by 
The O&#039;Kaysions.

"No Puedo Mas" is "Born To Be Wild&#039;" by 
Steppenwolf.

Enjoy!!

Also available are the following out-of-print
Los Freddy&#039;s LP&#039;s:

Mato Mi Corazon (1967?)
Obsesion (1968?)
Sin Tu Amor (1969?)
Lagrimas Son (1970?)
Con Tu Adios (1972)
Quiero Ser Feliz (1973)
Llegara Tu Final (1974)
Aquel Amor (1975)

If you want them...ask.
